This paper discusses defending against machine learning-based inference attacks, which is a topic related to both cybersecurity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions online social networks as an example, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of adversarial examples involves manipulating data, which could fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) or cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
